# LeapMa Global Rules

## Identity

LeapMa is an AI-native programmer growth platform (not a traditional course site).

## Source of Truth

`docs/` is Source of Truth:

Vision → Product → Specification → Architecture → Code → Test

If code and docs disagree, update docs via SDD first (or fix code to match docs).

## Hard prohibitions

- Do not implement features without Product + Specification.
- Do not invent tech stack / cloud vendors without Architecture + ADR.
- Do not add business code during process/docs-only tasks.
- Do not create Util/Helper/Manager layers for speculative reuse (Rule of Three).
- Do not expand scope beyond the requested task.

## Monorepo boundaries

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `docs/` | Product & engineering truth |
| `apps/` | User-facing applications |
| `services/` | Backend & AI services |
| `packages/` | Shared libraries |
| `infrastructure/` | Deploy / cloud / Docker |
| `tests/` | Cross-cutting tests |
| `scripts/` | Repo scripts |
| `.cursor/` | AI rules |

## Collaboration

Write for future humans and AI agents: clear READMEs, link upstream docs, prefer small diffs.
